Personal Computers (PCs):
Personal computers are designed for individual use.

Examples:
Desktop computers
Laptops

Characteristics:
General-purpose use
Used for browsing, work, and applications
Found in homes and offices

Servers
Servers are powerful computers designed to provide services to other devices over a network.

Common services:

Websites (web servers)
File storage
Databases
Authentication systems

Characteristics:
High performance
Always running (24/7)
Often located in data centers

Servers are critical targets in cyberattacks due to the sensitive data they store.

Mobile Devices
Mobile devices are portable computing systems.

Examples:
Smartphones
Tablets

Characteristics:
Wireless connectivity (Wi-Fi, mobile data)
Limited processing power compared to servers
High user interaction

Embedded Systems

Embedded systems are specialized computers built into larger devices.

Examples:
Smart TVs
Traffic lights
Cars
IoT devices (smart thermostats, cameras)

Characteristics:
Perform specific tasks
Limited user interaction
Often resource-constrained
Mainframe Computers

Mainframes are large, powerful systems used for processing massive amounts of data.

Used by:
Banks
Governments
Large corporations

Characteristics:
Extremely reliable
High processing power
Support thousands of simultaneous users

Client vs Server Model

Client
A device that requests services or resources.

Example:
Web browser requesting a webpage

Server
A device that provides services or resources.

Example:

Web server hosting a website

Why does this matter in cybersecurity?

Different computer types have different risk profiles:

PCs are often targeted by malware and phishing
Servers are targeted for data theft and disruption
Mobile devices are vulnerable to app-based attacks
Embedded systems may have weak security and are hard to patch

Key Takeaways:
Computers come in different types based on purpose.
Servers provide services, while clients request them.
Embedded systems are specialized and often overlooked in security.
Understanding system types helps identify potential attack targets.
